      {
        "id": 269612,
        "name": "Atomik Circus",
        "username": "Atomik_Circus",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/atomik_circus/{size}/52511_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-06-11T17:09:06.970Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello Signal team,</p>\n<p>First of all, thank you for the amazing work you’re doing—Signal is an essential tool in my daily communication, and I deeply appreciate your commitment to privacy and usability.</p>\n<p>I’d like to request a feature that would significantly improve the experience during video calls: the ability to detach the video call window from the main Signal Desktop app. This becomes especially important when screen sharing .currently, it’s difficult to use the chat interface while in a call because the video and chat are stuck in the same window.</p>\n<p>A detachable call window would allow users to:</p>\n<pre><code>Continue chatting while on a call without awkwardly resizing windows.\n\nKeep an eye on the call while working in other parts of the app or on shared content.\n\nGenerally enhance multitasking and usability during video meetings.\n</code></pre>\n<p>This small UI/UX improvement would have a big impact on productivity and ease of use during calls.</p>\n<p>Thanks again for all your hard work—please keep it going! I fully respect and admire the dedication of the developers behind Signal.</p>\n<p>Best regards,<br>\n/ben</p>",
        "post_number": 11,
        "post_type": 1,
